                                                // Max length of s is 2*10^5.
                                                // So if len_binary_part is too large, current_val will exceed N.
                                                // If current_val > N, then it cannot be equal to j-i+1 (which is <= N).
                                                // So we can stop early.
                                                // The maximum length of the substring s[i...j] is N.
                                                // The value current_val is at most 2^len_binary_part - 1.
                                                // If len_binary_part is 18, current_val <= 2^18-1 approx 2.6*10^5.
                                                // If len_binary_part is 19, current_val <= 2^19-1 approx 5.2*10^5.
                                                // So we can iterate up to len_binary_part = 19.
                                                // This means j - first_one_idx + 1 <= 19.
                                                // So j <= first_one_idx + 18.
                        break;
                    }
                    current_val = (current_val << 1) | (s[j] - '0');

