                                    // If current_val > N, it cannot be equal to len.
                                    // If len is 20, current_val can be 20.
                                    // The condition is current_val == len.
                                    // If len > 19, then current_val will be at least 2^(len-1).
                                    // For len=20, current_val >= 2^19.
                                    // 2^19 is approx 5*10^5.
                                    // N is 2*10^5.
