                                    // If len=18, current_val >= 2^17 approx 1.3*10^5.
                                    // So if len >= 19, current_val will be >= 2^18.
                                    // But len is at most N = 2*10^5.
                                    // So if len >= 19, current_val will be much larger than len.
                                    // Example: len=19, current_val >= 2^18. 19 != 2^18.
                                    // So we only need to check for len up to 18.
                                    // This means j <= i + 17.
