                // For L >= 3, L < 2^(L-1).
                // So, if s[i] == '1', good substrings can only have length 1 or 2.
                // Length 1: s[i] = '1'. Value 1, length 1. Good.
                // Length 2: s[i...i+1] = "10" or "11".
                // "10": value 2, length 2. Good.
                // "11": value 3, length 2. Not good.
                // So, for s[i] == '1', we only need to check s[i] and s[i...i+1].
                // This is already covered by the loop above (j <= i+17).
                // The loop for s[i] == '1' should be:
                // for (int j = i; j < n; ++j) {
