        // If (k - m) is odd, we must use one axial move pair.
        // For example, (x,y) -> (x+1,y) -> (x,y) -> (x+1,y+1) -> (x,y+1).
        // This is not quite right.
        // The total number of moves is k.
        // We need to reach (n, m).
        // The minimum number of moves is m.
        // We can make n diagonal moves to reach (n, n).
        // We can make m-n axial moves to reach (n, m).
        // This uses m moves.
