        // If k-m is odd, we have (k-m-1) moves that can be diagonal pairs, and 1 move that must be axial.
        // The (k-m-1) moves contribute (k-m-1) diagonal moves.
        // The remaining 1 move must be an axial move, which means it contributes 0 diagonal moves.
        // So, total diagonal moves = n (to reach (n,n)) + (k - m - 1) (from wasting).
        // This simplifies to k - (m - n) - 1.
